Class NEW

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NonCallingBytecode

    public class NEW
extends NonCallingSequentialBytecode
    A bytecode that creates an object of a given class and pushes it on top of the stack. Note that the constructor is not called on the newly created object.

    ... -> ..., new object
    Author:
    Fausto Spoto
